01:00:33.489 --> 01:00:35.670
- You're not
joining him?

1019
01:00:35.770 --> 01:00:38.351
- You didn't ask me here
to hunt.

1020
01:00:38.451 --> 01:00:40.551
I'm here to talk cattle.

1021
01:00:40.651 --> 01:00:42.872
- They don't belong to you.

1022
01:00:42.972 --> 01:00:45.273
- They don't belong
to you either.

1023
01:00:45.373 --> 01:00:47.114
They belong to the people now.

1024
01:00:47.214 --> 01:00:49.115
- Every one of them
wears a brand.

1025
01:00:49.215 --> 01:00:50.835
If anybody tries
to move them off the Res--

1026
01:00:50.935 --> 01:00:52.876
- They'll never leave the Res.

1027
01:00:52.976 --> 01:00:56.997
We'll use them to raise calves.
wear our brand.

1028
01:00:57.097 --> 01:00:59.078
- I understand
your position. Thomas.

1029
01:00:59.178 --> 01:01:01.279
and what you think
you need to do...

1030
01:01:01.379 --> 01:01:03.200
but I won't allow you
to make

1031
01:01:03.300 --> 01:01:04.840
victims of the people
who elected me

1032
01:01:04.940 --> 01:01:07.401
just to appease the people
who elected you.

1033
01:01:07.501 --> 01:01:10.342
- Your people don't know
the concept of victim.

1034
01:01:13.944 --> 01:01:16.765
- Let's keep this about
cattle.

1035
01:01:16.865 --> 01:01:18.845
If you act like
a thief. Thomas.

1036
01:01:18.945 --> 01:01:20.966
I will treat you like one.

1037
01:01:21.066 --> 01:01:22.687
- How can you stand there
on a ranch

1038
01:01:22.787 --> 01:01:24.407
the size of Rhode Island

1039
01:01:24.507 --> 01:01:26.648
and accuse me of theft?

1040
01:01:26.748 --> 01:01:29.569
Is this your idea of respect?

1041
01:01:29.669 --> 01:01:32.490
Letting some crippled old man
ride his lame horse

1042
01:01:32.590 --> 01:01:34.571
out toward
your half-tame buffalo

1043
01:01:34.671 --> 01:01:36.172
so he can pretend
to be something

1044
01:01:36.272 --> 01:01:39.173
we haven't been in a century?

1045
01:01:39.273 --> 01:01:42.094
<i>[somber music]</i>

1046
01:01:42.194 --> 01:01:45.575
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1047
01:01:45.675 --> 01:01:47.756
- Whoo!

1048
01:01:49.076 --> 01:01:51.017
- Look what you've
reduced us to.

1049
01:01:51.117 --> 01:01:53.118
[clicks tongue]

1050
01:01:59.880 --> 01:02:01.301
- Here's another one.

1051
01:02:01.401 --> 01:02:04.462
[chicken clucking]

1052
01:02:04.562 --> 01:02:06.763
You lay everywhere
but the coop.

1053
01:02:10.564 --> 01:02:12.645
[children chattering]

1054
01:02:17.047 --> 01:02:18.467
- [speaking native language]

1055
01:02:18.567 --> 01:02:20.608
- [speaking
native language]

1056
01:02:28.291 --> 01:02:29.471
Backstraps.

1057
01:02:29.571 --> 01:02:31.072
- Staying for dinner?
- Can't.

1058
01:02:31.172 --> 01:02:33.793
Just need a few words
with this young buck here.

1059
01:02:33.893 --> 01:02:35.753
Can you give us a minute?

1060
01:02:35.853 --> 01:02:39.115
- If you can say it to him.
you can say it to me.

1061
01:02:39.215 --> 01:02:43.036
- Hard to talk about you when
you're standing here. darling.

1062
01:02:43.136 --> 01:02:46.097
- Come on. Tate.
We're being sent to our room.

1063
01:02:48.218 --> 01:02:50.419
- The Nation will
keep the cattle.

1064
01:02:51.259 --> 01:02:54.160
Your father will try
to take them back.

1065
01:02:54.260 --> 01:02:56.681
He has every right.

1066
01:02:56.781 --> 01:03:01.623
We had every right to take
them. so now we will fight.

1067
01:03:03.343 --> 01:03:06.004
- It's his fight. not mine.

1068
01:03:06.104 --> 01:03:10.646
- You will be judged
for the actions of your father.

1069
01:03:10.746 --> 01:03:14.127
If you do nothing. you will
be judged for that too.

1070
01:03:14.227 --> 01:03:16.568
They all will.

1071
01:03:16.668 --> 01:03:20.450
Maybe it's best you go home
for a while. eh?

1072
01:03:20.550 --> 01:03:22.170
- This is my home.

1073
01:03:22.270 --> 01:03:24.591
- You know what I mean.

1074
01:03:27.312 --> 01:03:29.433
- I've been nothing
but a friend to everybody here.

1075
01:03:30.673 --> 01:03:31.894
If somebody wants me to leave.

1076
01:03:31.994 --> 01:03:33.975
you can tell them
to come make me.

1077
01:03:34.075 --> 01:03:37.036
- Pretty silly thing to say
on a reservation.

1078
01:03:38.516 --> 01:03:40.857
I don't ask much.

1079
01:03:40.957 --> 01:03:43.578
but I'm asking you this.

1080
01:03:43.678 --> 01:03:45.779
Go home.

1081
01:03:45.879 --> 01:03:49.380
Take care of my granddaughter.

1082
01:03:49.480 --> 01:03:52.021
Be good to that boy.

1083
01:03:52.121 --> 01:03:55.902
Until they find a cure
for human nature.

1084
01:03:56.002 --> 01:03:58.763
a man must stand
with his people.

1085
01:04:03.245 --> 01:04:06.826
And we are not your people.

1086
01:04:06.926 --> 01:04:09.908
<i>[somber music]</i>

1087
01:04:10.008 --> 01:04:15.209
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1088
01:04:22.092 --> 01:04:24.393
- Hey.
Hey. Jimmy!

1089
01:04:24.493 --> 01:04:25.873
Let's go.
You're late.

1090
01:04:25.973 --> 01:04:28.214
Let's go. You're late.

1091
01:04:29.495 --> 01:04:32.276
You know how to ride a horse?
- Uh...

1092
01:04:32.376 --> 01:04:34.557
- Figures. Come here.
Give me your shit.

1093
01:04:34.657 --> 01:04:36.277
Let's go.
That there is Ron.

1094
01:04:36.377 --> 01:04:38.578
You do whatever the hell
he asks you to do.

1095
01:04:39.458 --> 01:04:42.239
Come on. get on.
Get on the horse.

1096
01:04:42.339 --> 01:04:44.340
- I don't--

1097
01:04:44.780 --> 01:04:46.781
- Get on the horse. Jimmy.

1098
01:04:50.262 --> 01:04:53.363
Pull the reins to stop.
Kick him in the belly to go.

1099
01:04:53.463 --> 01:04:55.464
All right. let's move.

1100
01:05:03.387 --> 01:05:05.388
- Both in one night?

1101
01:05:06.908 --> 01:05:09.149
- Everyone's forgotten
who runs this valley.

1102
01:05:10.710 --> 01:05:12.710
- So this is how you
remind them?

1103
01:05:13.431 --> 01:05:15.011
This is not the way
to remind them. It's a--

1104
01:05:15.111 --> 01:05:17.092
It's a bad idea.

1105
01:05:17.192 --> 01:05:19.193
- We don't choose the way.
little brother.

1106
01:05:21.193 --> 01:05:23.674
[helicopter powering up]

1107
01:05:45.802 --> 01:05:48.703
<i>[Pucifer's "Tumbleweed"]</i>

1108
01:05:48.803 --> 01:05:55.686
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1109
01:05:59.887 --> 01:06:02.749
- Dad.
I'm the fastest runner.

1110
01:06:02.849 --> 01:06:04.849
I'm bucking.
I'm bucking.

1111
01:06:06.450 --> 01:06:08.511
And he falls.

1112
01:06:08.611 --> 01:06:10.611
[thud]
[laughs]

1113
01:06:12.012 --> 01:06:14.913
<i>- ♪ Home ♪</i>

1114
01:06:15.013 --> 01:06:20.395
<i>♪ A candle you can hold.</i>
<i>you're not alone ♪</i>

1115
01:06:20.495 --> 01:06:24.637
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1116
01:06:24.737 --> 01:06:27.918
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

1117
01:06:28.018 --> 01:06:33.880
<i>♪ So far away.</i>
<i>come on home ♪</i>

1118
01:06:33.980 --> 01:06:37.281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1119
01:06:37.381 --> 01:06:40.162
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

1120
01:06:40.262 --> 01:06:46.765
<i>♪ A voice from within.</i>
<i>you're not alone ♪</i>

1121
01:06:46.865 --> 01:06:53.707
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1122
01:07:14.835 --> 01:07:18.296
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

1123
01:07:18.396 --> 01:07:24.458
<i>♪ A candle you can hold.</i>
<i>you're not alone ♪</i>

1124
01:07:24.558 --> 01:07:27.779
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1125
01:07:27.879 --> 01:07:30.821
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

1126
01:07:30.921 --> 01:07:37.143
<i>♪ You're so far away.</i>
<i>come on home ♪</i>

1127
01:07:37.243 --> 01:07:40.464
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1128
01:07:40.564 --> 01:07:42.825
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

1129
01:07:42.925 --> 01:07:49.587
<i>♪ A voice from within.</i>
<i>you're not alone ♪</i>

1130
01:07:49.687 --> 01:07:53.189
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1131
01:07:53.289 --> 01:07:56.070
<i>♪ Home ♪</i>

1132
01:07:56.170 --> 01:08:00.912
<i>♪ You're so far away.</i>
<i>come on home ♪</i>

1133
01:08:01.012 --> 01:08:03.412
[drill whirring]

1134
01:08:05.653 --> 01:08:07.654
- This is the last one.

1135
01:08:09.134 --> 01:08:11.655
Jimmy. hey.
get your ass up here.

1136
01:08:13.856 --> 01:08:15.557
- I just saw a trout.
- Shut the fuck up.

1137
01:08:15.657 --> 01:08:17.738
Crank this thing
until I tell you to stop.

1138
01:08:28.822 --> 01:08:30.282
- Holy shit. is this legal?

1139
01:08:30.382 --> 01:08:32.323
- You're a criminal.
What do you care?

1140
01:08:32.423 --> 01:08:33.343
- I thought the oldest Dutton
was gonna

1141
01:08:33.423 --> 01:08:34.364
keep me out of trouble.

1142
01:08:34.464 --> 01:08:35.364
- Getting in trouble's

1143
01:08:35.464 --> 01:08:36.484
the only skill you got.

1144
01:08:36.584 --> 01:08:37.565
The only difference now is

1145
01:08:37.665 --> 01:08:39.986
you ain't gonna get caught.

1146
01:08:47.628 --> 01:08:49.449
Start moving it down
to the river. Let's go.

1147
01:08:49.549 --> 01:08:51.550
That's good enough.

1148
01:08:59.513 --> 01:09:01.754
Start moving it this way now.

1149
01:09:03.874 --> 01:09:06.335
Hey. quit looking at fish.

1150
01:09:06.435 --> 01:09:09.616
[indistinct chatter]

1151
01:09:09.716 --> 01:09:13.258
[quiet piano notes]

1152
01:09:13.358 --> 01:09:21.321
♪ ♪

1153
01:09:30.364 --> 01:09:32.365
- Hi. Marian. how are you?
- Hi. how are you?

1154
01:09:35.366 --> 01:09:37.947
Hello.
- Hello.

1155
01:09:38.047 --> 01:09:41.348
[piano music continues]

1156
01:09:41.448 --> 01:09:42.789
♪ ♪

1157
01:09:42.889 --> 01:09:46.190
- Sir?
- Thank you.

1158
01:09:46.290 --> 01:09:50.071
♪ ♪

1159
01:09:50.171 --> 01:09:52.592
How are we all doing here?
- Oh. good!

1160
01:09:52.692 --> 01:09:54.193
- It's been a long time.
Yes.

1161
01:09:54.293 --> 01:09:56.594
- Thank you for coming by.
- You look well.

1162
01:09:56.694 --> 01:09:59.074
- Thank you for joining me.

1163
01:09:59.174 --> 01:10:01.355
Bye.

1164
01:10:01.455 --> 01:10:04.436
[background chatter]

1165
01:10:04.536 --> 01:10:10.659
♪ ♪

1166
01:10:22.743 --> 01:10:24.744
- I feel different here.

1167
01:10:26.064 --> 01:10:28.065
My skin tingles.

1168
01:10:29.706 --> 01:10:31.706
Never felt like this before.

1169
01:10:32.787 --> 01:10:35.848
- That's because you live
in the city.

1170
01:10:35.948 --> 01:10:39.409
Cities are the sunsets
of civilization...

1171
01:10:39.509 --> 01:10:41.710
monuments
to an exhausted landscape.

1172
01:10:45.751 --> 01:10:49.773
Man is migratory by nature.

1173
01:10:49.873 --> 01:10:53.934
What you're feeling
is instinct...

1174
01:10:54.034 --> 01:10:57.996
a hunger for new land
that's woven into your DNA.

1175
01:10:59.877 --> 01:11:01.417
That's the reason
our species survived

1176
01:11:01.517 --> 01:11:03.678
when countless others failed.

1177
01:11:06.839 --> 01:11:09.780
That tingle

1178
01:11:09.880 --> 01:11:12.881
is the sensation
of touching your destiny.

1179
01:11:16.242 --> 01:11:19.043
[explosions booming]

1180
01:11:23.645 --> 01:11:26.506
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

1181
01:11:26.606 --> 01:11:30.068
- The fuck was that?
[booming echoes]

1182
01:11:30.168 --> 01:11:32.168
- Oh. no.

1183
01:11:49.014 --> 01:11:50.555
- We hold here.
- Hold up here.

1184
01:11:50.655 --> 01:11:51.835
They're coming.

1185
01:11:51.935 --> 01:11:53.936
<i>- We're in position.</i>

1186
01:11:58.898 --> 01:12:00.899
[cow lows]

1187
01:12:02.219 --> 01:12:05.160
<i>- Ready?</i>
<i>- Yeah.</i>

1188
01:12:05.260 --> 01:12:06.681
- Hold on.

1189
01:12:06.781 --> 01:12:08.822
[helicopter whirring]

1190
01:12:11.783 --> 01:12:13.923
- Get ready.

1191
01:12:14.023 --> 01:12:15.044
They're coming.

1192
01:12:15.144 --> 01:12:17.145
[cocks gun]

1193
01:12:17.585 --> 01:12:19.045
- Let 'em.

1194
01:12:19.145 --> 01:12:22.046
<i>[dramatic music building]</i>

1195
01:12:22.146 --> 01:12:28.829
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1196
01:12:40.433 --> 01:12:42.574
- Let's get out of here!

1197
01:12:42.674 --> 01:12:44.695
Robert. let's go!

1198
01:12:44.795 --> 01:12:47.075
[cattle lowing]

1199
01:12:51.557 --> 01:12:53.558
<i>- Lee. get in there.</i>

1200
01:12:54.598 --> 01:12:56.179
- Yah. yah!

1201
01:12:56.279 --> 01:13:00.220
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

1202
01:13:00.320 --> 01:13:01.701
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1203
01:13:01.801 --> 01:13:03.141
- Who's that?
Is that one of ours?

1204
01:13:03.241 --> 01:13:05.242
- Yah! Yah!
- Hit him with the light.

1205
01:13:07.923 --> 01:13:10.564
- Yah! Yah. yah!
<i>- What the hell's he doing?</i>

1206
01:13:12.885 --> 01:13:14.586
- God damn that boy.

1207
01:13:14.686 --> 01:13:16.686
<i>Get behind him.</i>

1208
01:13:17.887 --> 01:13:19.887
Now take us down.

1209
01:13:26.370 --> 01:13:27.750
- You see that?

1210
01:13:27.850 --> 01:13:29.851
Jesus Christ!

1211
01:13:37.294 --> 01:13:39.635
- No. Hold your fire.

1212
01:13:39.735 --> 01:13:41.735
<i>- What do we do now?</i>

1213
01:13:42.175 --> 01:13:43.756
- Pull back.

1214
01:13:43.856 --> 01:13:46.217
Pull back. Abort.

1215
01:13:48.258 --> 01:13:50.258
<i>Everybody pull back.</i>

1216
01:13:57.861 --> 01:13:59.562
- Put your gun down!

1217
01:13:59.662 --> 01:14:01.663
[overlapping shouting]
[cattle lowing]

1218
01:14:03.343 --> 01:14:05.164
- We got to get
the fuck out of here.

1219
01:14:05.264 --> 01:14:06.925
- We ain't going anywhere
without our beef.

1220
01:14:07.025 --> 01:14:09.285
- Hold them back!

1221
01:14:09.385 --> 01:14:12.607
Get over in front of them!
Hold them back!

1222
01:14:12.707 --> 01:14:14.767
[gunshots]

1223
01:14:14.867 --> 01:14:16.868
- Yah! Yah!

1224
01:14:17.508 --> 01:14:19.509
Yah!

1225
01:14:26.352 --> 01:14:28.652
- 40 tours in Afghanistan.
and I got to deal

1226
01:14:28.752 --> 01:14:30.533
with this shit
in fucking Montana.

1227
01:14:30.633 --> 01:14:32.654
- Wheel us around.
- Jesus Christ. John.

1228
01:14:32.754 --> 01:14:34.535
we got to get out of here.
- I said wheel us around!

1229
01:14:34.635 --> 01:14:36.535
<i>We've still got men</i>
<i>down there.</i>

1230
01:14:36.635 --> 01:14:38.496
Drop us down and push
those bastards back.

1231
01:14:38.596 --> 01:14:40.597
- Yes. sir.

1232
01:14:42.878 --> 01:14:43.858
- Closer.

1233
01:14:43.958 --> 01:14:45.959
- Hang on.

1234
01:14:50.520 --> 01:14:53.882
[overlapping shouting]

1235
01:15:00.964 --> 01:15:02.965
<i>All right. we're through.</i>

1236
01:15:04.445 --> 01:15:06.886
[men shouting. whistling]

1237
01:15:11.488 --> 01:15:14.229
[gunfire]

1238
01:15:14.329 --> 01:15:16.330
- Keep them moving.

1239
01:15:23.932 --> 01:15:26.473
You want 'em back.
come and get 'em!

1240
01:15:26.573 --> 01:15:29.354
<i>[heavy music]</i>

1241
01:15:29.454 --> 01:15:34.676
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1242
01:15:34.776 --> 01:15:36.777
[gunshot]
Oh!

1243
01:15:42.539 --> 01:15:44.540
[groaning]

1244
01:15:51.462 --> 01:15:53.463
- I want them back.

1245
01:16:03.667 --> 01:16:05.168
- Hang on. okay?

1246
01:16:05.268 --> 01:16:07.268
I'm gonna get you out of here.

1247
01:16:08.549 --> 01:16:11.490
- Look at you...
you're a man now.

1248
01:16:11.590 --> 01:16:14.491
<i>[somber music]</i>

1249
01:16:14.591 --> 01:16:18.172
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1250
01:16:18.272 --> 01:16:20.273
[click. click]

1251
01:16:28.836 --> 01:16:31.057
- In case you don't
already know.

1252
01:16:31.157 --> 01:16:33.158
there's no such thing
as heaven.

1253
01:16:41.881 --> 01:16:43.882
Hey.

1254
01:16:52.645 --> 01:16:55.586
<i>[dark. emotional music]</i>

1255
01:16:55.686 --> 01:17:02.768
<i>♪ ♪</i>

1256
01:17:06.610 --> 01:17:10.131
[sobbing]

1257
01:17:24.976 --> 01:17:26.877
- Yes. sir. yeah. I hear you.
Give me four mounted agents

1258
01:17:26.977 --> 01:17:28.918
and four agents on ATVs
out there right now.

1259
01:17:29.018 --> 01:17:31.019
Yes.

1260
01:17:31.699 --> 01:17:33.760
I hear--okay.

1261
01:17:33.860 --> 01:17:35.640
Okay. thank you.

1262
01:17:35.740 --> 01:17:37.741
Thank you.

1263
01:17:38.942 --> 01:17:40.442
All right. state police
are sending

1264
01:17:40.542 --> 01:17:42.543
a chopper out
to look for him.

1265
01:17:47.905 --> 01:17:49.645
- Tell them to hold off.

1266
01:17:49.745 --> 01:17:51.946
I found him.

1267
01:18:19.156 --> 01:18:21.257
Give me the reins.

1268
01:18:21.357 --> 01:18:23.378
Give me the reins.

1269
01:18:23.478 --> 01:18:25.659
All right.

